                <h1 class="text-center text-primary mb-4">Visitor Pass System</h1>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Technology Stack</h4>
                    <p>ASP.NET, C#, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, SQL Server</p>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Project Overview</h4>
                    <p>
                        I developed a comprehensive Inventory Management System to streamline the management of product stock, orders, and reports.
                        This system addresses the critical needs of inventory tracking and control, offering businesses a reliable solution for efficient
                        operations and data-driven decision-making.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Key Highlights</h4>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>User Interface:</strong> The system’s front-end was crafted using HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap, resulting in a responsive
                            and user-friendly design. The interface is intuitive, ensuring ease of use for both administrators and visitors.
                            Its responsive design guarantees accessibility across various devices, including desktops, tablets, and smartphones,
                            providing a consistent experience for all users.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Backend Development:</strong> The backend, developed using ASP.NET and C#, ensures structured, scalable, and maintainable code.
                            The ASP.NET framework facilitated the seamless integration of core functionalities, while C# enabled efficient handling of processes like
                            visitor registration, pass issuance, and activity logging. The backend architecture supports future scalability and adaptability for evolving
                            requirements.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Database:</strong> The system employs SQL Server as the database, ensuring reliable and efficient data storage.
                            Key database functionalities include:.
                            <ul class="list-group">
                                <li class="list-group-item">
                                    <strong>Visitor Registration:</strong>Captures and stores visitor details such as name, contact information, purpose of visit, and host details.
                                </li>
                                <li class="list-group-item">
                                    <strong>Pass Management:</strong>Records pass issuance details, including pass ID, validity, and status.
                                </li>
                                <li class="list-group-item">
                                    <strong>Entry and Exit Logs:</strong> Maintains a detailed log of visitor entries and exits for enhanced security and auditability.
                                </li>
                                <li class="list-group-item">
                                    <strong>Notifications: </strong> Tracks pass expiry and triggers alerts for timely renewal or termination.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Core Features</h4>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>User Authentication:</strong> Secure login with role-based access control.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Visitor Registration:</strong>Quick and straightforward registration process for visitors, capturing essential details for identification and security.
                            Option to pre-register visitors to streamline the check-in process.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Pass Issuance:</strong>Generates unique passes for each visitor, specifying validity and access permissions.
                            Supports different pass types (e.g., temporary, recurring).
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Entry and Exit:</strong>Tracks visitor movement in real time, logging entry and exit times for enhanced facility security.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Pass Expiry Notification:</strong>Sends automated alerts for expiring or expired passes to ensure timely action.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Reporting and Analytics:</strong>Generates detailed reports on visitor statistics, including frequency, duration of visits, and host details.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Security Measures</h4>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <Strong>Admin-Controlled Access:</Strong> Implemented role-based access control to restrict sensitive operations to administrators, ensuring data confidentiality and integrity.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <Strong>Data Validation:</Strong>Enforced input validation on both client and server sides to prevent vulnerabilities such as SQL injection and data tampering.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <Strong>Activity Monitoring:</Strong>Logs administrative actions for accountability and transparency.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
